      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_76gc' title='Col. 76GC &mdash; HL Deb 22 January 1998 vol 584 c76GC' name='column_76gc' href='#column_76gc' rel='bookmark'>76GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05109'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980122_GCR_61' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Redesdale</span> had given notice of his intention to move Amendment No. 23:
        <q>Page 9, line 40, at end insert (", including such persons as appear to him to represent local government").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05110'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980122_GCR_62' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: The Minister gave a very full assurance at the previous stage that he would consult local government on these amendments, and in the light of that, I will not move the amendment.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05111'>
