        [<span class="italic">Amendment No. 31 not moved.</span>]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05197'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980122_GCR_149' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</span> moved Amendment No. 32:
        <q>Page 14, line 5, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
        <q>("(6) In paragraph 3 of that Schedule (tenure of office) in sub-paragraph (4)(a) (removal on grounds of absence from meetings) for "or (as the case may be) from meetings of the committee without the committee's consent" there shall be substituted "or from meetings of a committee of the Board without the committee's consent".").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05198'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980122_GCR_150' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: In moving Amendment No. 32, I should like to speak also to Amendment No. 46. These amendments correct the inadvertent removal of a provision in the 1993 Act allowing for the removal of board or committee members of the National Lottery
        
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_93gc' title='Col. 93GC &mdash; HL Deb 22 January 1998 vol 584 c93GC' name='column_93gc' href='#column_93gc' rel='bookmark'>93GC</a>
        Charities Board from meetings of its committees. The amendments mean that unauthorised absence from meetings of board committees will continue to be grounds for removal from office, as is continued unauthorised absence from board meetings. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0584P0-05199'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0584P0_19980122_GCR_151' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
